(1)\ \tan^2(\frac{1}{2}\theta) = \frac{\tan(\theta) - \sin(\theta)}{\tan(\theta)+\sin(\theta)}
(2)\ \tan^2(\frac{1}{2}\theta)=\frac{1 - \cos(\theta)}{1 + \cos(\theta)} = \frac{\left(\frac{1 - \cos(\theta)}{2}\right)}{\left(\frac{1 + \cos(\theta)}{2}\right)}
\frac{\tan(\theta) - \sin(\theta)}{\tan(\theta)+\sin(\theta)}=\frac{\sin(\theta)/\cos\theta - \sin(\theta)}{\sin(\theta)/\cos\theta+\sin(\theta)}=\frac{1/\cos\theta - 1}{1/\cos\theta+1}=\frac{1-\cos\theta }{1+\cos\theta}
\frac{1 - \cos(\theta)}{1 + \cos(\theta)}=\frac{1 -1+ 2\sin^2(\theta/2)}{1 + 2\cos^2(\theta/2)-1}=\frac{\sin^2(\theta/2)}{\cos^2(\theta/2)}=\tan^2(\theta/2)
